fields.title: It's not art house, but...
fields.content: Memento is a very well made, very unique thriller/ crime drama. it does present an interesting character study and makes for a thought provoking watch. ... It's good, so definitely watch it.

fields.title: Leon The Professional is overrated
fields.content: It's a rubbish film. The relationship between Matilda and Leon was uncomfortable viewing (i was watching the director's cut). A 12 year old seducing a middle aged hitman and he subsequently getting flustered and hot under the collar. Come on. Leon revealing he hadn't had a girlfriend for a very long time, since he was younger was akin to that of Lolita. In fact the relationship resembled a soft version of Lolita, it was a disgusting subplot!

fields.title: kid friendly movie.
fields.content: While it is based on a comic book and previous instalments of 'Batman' in film and TV have been very child friendly, 'The Dark Knight' is definitely a movie for adults. The excessive use of violence throughout and the unpredictable, psychopathic nature of The Joker is likely to be too frightening for most children.

fields.title: too long but worth
fields.content: "The Green Mile" is a little too long, but the captivating performances from Tom Hanks and Michael Clarke Duncan make it worth it. It is without a doubt one of the best Stephen King adaptations ever made.

fields.title: instant, lasting cultural impact
fields.content:
The Matrix made an instant, lasting cultural impact

It won Academy Awards for Best Film Editing, Best Visual Effects, Best Sound, and Best Sound Editing, sweeping the categories in which it was nominated.
